#            behind the self-hosted Coder cloud-development platform).
#            Wush is the "scp without an intermediate server" + "ssh
#            into a NATed machine without a jump host" + "rsync over
#            a peer-to-peer overlay" tool — uses the same **Tailscale
#            wireguard-go + DERP relay + STUN hole-punching stack**
#            that Tailscale itself uses, but spins up an ad-hoc
#            two-node ephemeral mesh between exactly two devices
#            authenticated by a one-time auth key.  No control-plane
#            account required.  No "share this link" cloud relay
#            required.  The receiving side runs `wush serve` and
#            prints an auth key;  the sending side runs `wush ssh
#            --auth-key <KEY>` or `wush cp --auth-key <KEY> file` and
#            gets a direct UDP-hole-punched WireGuard tunnel
#            (falling back to the public Tailscale DERP relay mesh
#            if the firewall blocks UDP).  Go=182 leader bump
#            continuing Axis 127 (pure-Rust + pure-Go SSH 2.0 protocol
#            implementation taxonomy) at 2/0/0 via the canonical
#            Go-side **github.com/gliderlabs/ssh** library (which
